The paper deals with the identification of dynamical properties and topology of structured interconnections of dynamical systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of predictor filters and noise-free node signals, which are relevant to machine learning and signal processing (cs.LG and cs.IT). The paper also mentions the estimation of network dynamics, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the incorporation of prior knowledge of network structure, which is relevant to information theory (cs.SI).
